text: Ashton-under-Lyne by-election may refer to one of five by-elections held in the British House of Commons constituency of Ashton-under-Lyne, in Lancashire: * 1920 Ashton-under-Lyne by-election * 1928 Ashton-under-Lyne by-election * 1931 Ashton-under-Lyne by-election * 1939 Ashton-under-Lyne by-election * 1945 Ashton-under-Lyne by-election ==See also== * Ashton-under-Lyne (UK Parliament constituency)
title: Ashton-under-Lyne by-election
